<subSubSection box="[151,843,547,574]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,843,547,574]" box="[151,843,547,574]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,843,547,574]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Braasch 1983" authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" box="[151,843,547,574]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum" subGenus="Caucasiron">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,843,547,574]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,252,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Epeorus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[269,409,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Caucasiron</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[427,667,547,574]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D." box="[674,843,547,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="195 - 196" refId="ref10005" refString="Braasch, D. (1983) Eintagsfliegen (Gattungen Epeorus und Iron) aus Nepal und Indien (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Reichenbachia, 21 (34), 195 - 196." type="journal article" year="1983">Braasch 1983</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="516" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,619,1186]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,619,645]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" box="[430,806,619,646]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum" subGenus="Caucasiron">
<emphasis box="[430,523,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Epeorus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[542,568,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">C.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[587,806,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the following combination of characters: in larva (i) margin of gills with spines; (ii) femora without any hypodermal femur spot; and (iii) claw without denticles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,657,727,754]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,619,1186]" box="[199,657,727,754]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,727,753]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[362,420,727,753]" name="India" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[434,645,727,754]" country="India" name="Himachal Pradesh" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Himachal Pradesh</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="516" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,619,1186]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,763,789]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kapur, A. P. &amp; Kripalani, M. B." box="[326,623,763,790]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="183 - 221" refId="ref10730" refString="Kapur, A. P. &amp; Kripalani, M. B. (1963) The mayflies (Ephemeroptera) from the north - western Himalaya. Records of the Indian Museum, 59, 183 - 221." type="journal article" year="1963">Kapur &amp; Kripalani (1963)</bibRefCitation>
studied the collections of Zoological Survey of 
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1231,763,789]" name="India" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">India</collectingCountry>
in May and June, 1955 from Kullu and the Lahaul-Spiti Valleys in Western Himalayas and recorded a species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1242,1347,800,825]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ironopsis">
<emphasis box="[1242,1347,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Ironopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but did not formally name the species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D." box="[504,677,835,861]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="195 - 196" refId="ref10005" refString="Braasch, D. (1983) Eintagsfliegen (Gattungen Epeorus und Iron) aus Nepal und Indien (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Reichenbachia, 21 (34), 195 - 196." type="journal article" year="1983">Braasch (1983)</bibRefCitation>
could not have access to those specimens but named it as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">I. kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Braasch, D." box="[320,505,871,898]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="79 - 88" refId="ref10076" refString="Braasch, D. (2006 a) Neue Eintagsfliegen der Gattungen Epeorus und Iron aus dem Himalaja (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Entomologische Nachrichten und Berichte, 50 (1 - 2), 79 - 88." type="journal article" year="2006">Braasch (2006a)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" box="[617,868,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum">
<emphasis box="[617,868,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brodsky" authorityYear="1930" box="[906,1126,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheophilus">
<emphasis box="[906,1126,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Epeorus rheophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but his grouping did not gain wide acceptance. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[610,749,907,933]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10770" refString="Kluge, N. J. (1989) Revision of genera of the family Heptageniidae (Ephemeroptera). I. Diagnoses of tribes, genera and subgenera of the subfamily Heptageniinae. Entomological Review, 68, 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1989">Kluge, 1989</bibRefCitation>
clearly recognized six subgenera of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1881" box="[1272,1365,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1272,1365,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Epeorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on valid morphological criteria. Based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[624,776,943,969]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref10770" refString="Kluge, N. J. (1989) Revision of genera of the family Heptageniidae (Ephemeroptera). I. Diagnoses of tribes, genera and subgenera of the subfamily Heptageniinae. Entomological Review, 68, 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1989">Kluge (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hrivniak, L. &amp; Sroka, P. &amp; Bojkova, J. &amp; Godunko, R. J." box="[788,1045,943,970]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 53" refId="ref10491" refString="Hrivniak, L., Sroka, P., Bojkova, J., Godunko, R. J. (2020 a) Identification guide to larvae of Caucasian Epeorus (Caucasiron) (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae) ZooKeys, 986, 1 - 53. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 986.56276" type="journal article" year="2020">
Hrivniak 
<emphasis box="[895,944,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">et al</emphasis>
. (2020 a
</bibRefCitation>
, b) the shape of gill II of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by Kapur &amp; Kripalani (1961, fig. 14b) indicate its inclusion in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kluge" authorityYear="1997" box="[1300,1430,980,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Caucasiron">
<emphasis box="[1300,1430,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Caucasiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[151,295,1015,1041]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="233 - 235" refId="ref10813" refString="Kluge, N. J. (1997) New subgenera of Holarctic mayflies (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae, Leptophlebiidae, Ephemerellidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 5 (2), 233 - 235. [1996]" type="journal article" year="1997">Kluge (1997</bibRefCitation>
, 2015) studied and described in detailed 
<taxonomicName authority="Brodsky, 1930" authorityName="Brodsky" authorityYear="1930" box="[754,1075,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheophilus">
<emphasis box="[754,904,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. rheophilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brodsky, K." box="[912,1075,1015,1041]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" pagination="681 - 720" refId="ref10322" refString="Brodsky, K. (1930) Zur Kenntnis der mittelasiatischen Ephemeropteren I. (Imagines). Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, 59, 681 - 720." type="journal article" year="1930">Brodsky, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and suggested the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,410,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalamorum">
<emphasis box="[151,410,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. kapurkripalamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brodsky" authorityYear="1930" box="[477,629,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheophilus">
<emphasis box="[477,629,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. rheophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which extends range of this species from Palearctic to Oriental realm. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" box="[269,521,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum">
<emphasis box="[269,521,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apparently belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kluge" authorityYear="1997" box="[905,1035,1088,1114]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="521" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Caucasiron">
<emphasis box="[905,1035,1088,1114]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Caucasiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
whereas 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge N. J." box="[1145,1297,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" refId="ref10852" refString="Kluge N. J. (2004) The phylogenetic system of Ephemeroptera. Kluwer Academic Publishers: 456 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 007 - 0872 - 3" type="book" year="2004">Kluge (2004)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brodsky" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheophilus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. rheophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[456,561,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ironopsis">
<emphasis box="[456,561,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">Ironopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Such ambiguities can be resolved only by future exploration in the 
<typeStatus box="[1318,1366,1124,1150]" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">type</typeStatus>
locality and association of life stages of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1983" box="[547,797,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapurkripalanorum">
<emphasis box="[547,797,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="516">E. kapurkripalanorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
